{
  "spec": "# Component Specification: Add / Edit Bookmark (Screen 2)\n\n**QuickMarks · PRD v1.0 · Planning Agent Output**\n\n---\n\n## 1. Component Tree\n\n```\nAddEditBookmarkPage\n├── PageHead                          [metadata: title tag, mode-driven]\n├── PageLayout                        [centering shell, background]\n│   ├── PageHeader\n│   │   ├── BackLink                  [← Bookmarks, navigates to /]\n│   │   └── PageTitle                 [<h1>, mode-driven text]\n│   │\n│   ├── DirtyFormWarningBar           [conditional render: dirty + cancel attempted]\n│   │   ├── WarningIcon               [⚠ SVG, decorative aria-hidden]\n│   │   ├── WarningMessage            [text node]\n│   │   ├── DiscardButton             [destructive action, navigates to /]\n│   │   └── KeepEditingButton         [dismisses bar, returns focus]\n│   │\n│   ├── NotFoundState                 [conditional render: edit mode, id not found]\n│   │   ├── ErrorHeading              [<h1> \"Bookmark Not Found\"]\n│   │   ├── ErrorSubMessage           [<p> sub-text]\n│   │   └── GoBackLink               [→ /]\n│   │\n│   └── BookmarkForm                  [<form novalidate>, max-width 480px, centered]\n│       ├── FieldGroup — Title\n│       │   ├── FieldLabel            [<label for=\"title\"> \"Title *\"]\n│       │   ├── TextInput             [id=\"title\", type=\"text\", maxlength=\"120\"]\n│       │   └── FieldError            [<span role=\"alert\", id=\"title-error\", conditional]\n│       │\n│       ├── FieldGroup — URL\n│       │   ├── FieldLabel            [<label for=\"url\"> \"URL *\"]\n│       │   ├── TextInput             [id=\"url\", type=\"url\"]\n│       │   │   └── HttpAdvisory      [lock-slash icon, conditional: http:// prefix]\n│       │   └── FieldError            [<span role=\"alert\", id=\"url-error\", conditional]\n│       │\n│       ├── FieldGroup — Tags\n│       │   ├── FieldLabel            [<label for=\"tags\"> \"Tags\" + OptionalBadge]\n│       │   ├── TagInputField\n│       │   │   ├── TagChipList       [committed chips, horizontal wrap]\n│       │   │   │   └── TagChip[]     [<span> + DismissButton per chip]\n│       │   │   │       └── DismissButton [aria-label=\"Remove tag: {name}\", ×]\n│       │   │   └── TagTextInput      [id=\"tags\", disabled when limit=5]\n│       │   ├── TagHelperText         [conditional: no active error, \"Up to 5 tags…\"]\n│       │   └── FieldError            [<span role=\"alert\", id=\"tags-error\", conditional]\n│       │\n│       ├── FieldGroup — Notes\n│       │   ├── FieldLabel            [<label for=\"notes\"> \"Notes\" + OptionalBadge]\n│       │   ├── Textarea              [id=\"notes\", rows=\"4\"]\n│       │   ├── CharacterCounter      [aria-live=\"polite\", \"{n} / 280\"]\n│       │   └── FieldError            [<span role=\"alert\", id=\"notes-error\", conditional]\n│       │\n│       └── FormActions\n│           ├── CancelButton          [ghost/text button]\n│           └── SubmitButton          [primary CTA, mode-driven label]\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Component Definitions\n\n### 2.1 `AddEditBookmarkPage`\n\n**Role:** Root orchestrator. Owns form state, validation state machine, dirty tracking, mode detection, and routing logic.\n\n**State owned:**\n```\nformValues:       { title, url, tags[], notes }\nfieldMeta:        { [fieldName]: { touched: bool, valid: bool, errorKey: string|null } }\nisDirty:          bool\nshowWarningBar:   bool\nmode:             'add' | 'edit' | 'not-found'\nbookmarkId:       string | null\nlastFocusedField: string | null        // for focus restoration on \"Keep editing\"\n```\n\n**Lifecycle:**\n- On mount (edit mode): call `BookmarkStore.getById(id)`. If null → set `mode = 'not-found'`. If found → pre-fill `formValues`, snapshot as `initialValues` for dirty comparison.\n- On mount (add mode): `formValues` all empty strings, `tags = []`.\n\n---\n\n### 2.2 `PageLayout`\n\n**Role:** Structural centering shell. Provides background colour and horizontal centering constraint.\n\n**Props:** `children`\n\n**Renders:** Full-viewport-height `<div>` with `background-primary` token.\n\n---\n\n### 2.3 `PageHeader`\n\n**Role:** Back navigation + page `<h1>`. Always visible except in `not-found` state (where `NotFoundState` provides its own heading).\n\n**Props:** `mode: 'add' | 'edit'`\n\n| Prop value | `<h1>` text | Document `<title>` |\n|---|---|---|\n| `add` | \"Add Bookmark\" | \"Add Bookmark — QuickMarks\" |\n| `edit` | \"Edit Bookmark\" | \"Edit Bookmark — QuickMarks\" |\n\n---\n\n### 2.4 `DirtyFormWarningBar`\n\n**Role:** Inline amber alert bar. Conditionally rendered. Announces via `role=\"alert\"` on mount so screen readers fire immediately.\n\n**Props:**\n```\nvisible:          bool\nonDiscard:        () => void    // navigate to /\nonKeepEditing:    () => void    // dismiss bar, restore focus\n```\n\n**Behaviour:**\n- Animates in with `normal` (200ms) `ease-out` fade + slide-down on `visible = true`.\n- Only one instance may exist in the DOM at a time.\n- Does not auto-dismiss.\n- `role=\"alert\"` on root element.\n\n---\n\n### 2.5 `NotFoundState`\n\n**Role:** Full replacement for the form when the edit target does not exist. Renders inside the same centered container.\n\n**Props:** none (static content)\n\n**Content:**\n- `<h1>` \"Bookmark Not Found\"\n- `<p>` \"This bookmark may have been deleted.\"\n- Link/button \"Go back to bookmarks\" → `/`\n\n---\n\n### 2.6 `BookmarkForm`\n\n**Role:** The `<form>` element. Houses all field groups and actions. Receives all form values and handlers as props from `AddEditBookmarkPage`.\n\n**Props:**\n```\nvalues:           FormValues\nfieldMeta:        FieldMetaMap\nmode:             'add' | 'edit'\nonFieldChange:    (field, value) => void\nonFieldBlur:      (field) => void\nonSubmit:         (e: Event) => void\nonCancel:         () => void\n```\n\n**Attributes:** `<form novalidate>` — suppresses all browser-native validation UI.\n\n---\n\n### 2.7 `FieldGroup`\n\n**Role:** Reusable layout wrapper composing a label, input, optional helper, and optional error message for a single form field.\n\n**Props:**\n```\nfieldId:          string\nlabel:            string\nrequired?:        bool\noptional?:        bool\nerror?:           string | null\nchildren:         ReactNode        // the actual input control\nhelperText?:      string\n```\n\n**Layout:** Vertical stack, `gap: 4px` between label and input, `gap: 4px` between input and error/helper.\n\n---\n\n### 2.8 `FieldLabel`\n\n**Role:** `<label>` element with required asterisk or optional badge.\n\n**Props:**\n```\nhtmlFor:          string\nrequired?:        bool\noptional?:        bool\nchildren:         string\n```\n\n**Renders:**\n- Required: `\"Title \"` + `<span aria-hidden=\"true\">*</span>` + visually hidden `<span> (required)</span>`\n- Optional: `\"Tags \"` + `<span class=\"optional-badge\">Optional</span>`\n\n---\n\n### 2.9 `TextInput`\n\n**Role:** Standard single-line text input. Used for Title and URL fields.\n\n**Props:**\n```\nid:               string\ntype:             'text' | 'url'\nvalue:            string\nplaceholder?:     string\nmaxLength?:       number\nrequired?:        bool\nhasError:         bool\nariaDescribedBy?: string\nonChange:         (value: string) => void\nonBlur:           () => void\n```\n\n**State-driven attribute bindings:**\n- `aria-invalid=\"true\"` when `hasError = true`\n- `aria-describedby={ariaDescribedBy}` always present (points to error span id)\n- `aria-required=\"true\"` when `required = true`\n- Border token: `border-default` → `border-focus` on focus → `border-error` when `hasError`\n\n---\n\n### 2.10 `TagInputField`\n\n**Role:** Composite tag entry control. Manages committed chips + live text input.\n\n**Props:**\n```\ntags:             string[]\ninputValue:       string\ndisabled:         bool                // true when tags.length === 5\nhasError:         bool\nariaDescribedBy:  string\nonTagAdd:         (tag: string) => void\nonTagRemove:      (index: number) => void\nonInputChange:    (value: string) => void\nonBlur:           () => void\n```\n\n**Internal behaviour:**\n- `,` or `Enter` keypress → trim → validate → call `onTagAdd` or surface error\n- `Backspace` on empty input → call `onTagRemove(tags.length - 1)`\n- When `disabled = true`: input has `disabled` attribute + helper text changes to \"Tag limit reached (5/5)\"\n\n---\n\n### 2.11 `TagChip`\n\n**Role:** Rendered committed tag pill with dismiss control.\n\n**Props:**\n```\nlabel:            string\nonRemove:         () => void\nindex:            number\n```\n\n**Accessibility:** Dismiss button carries `aria-label=\"Remove tag: {label}\"`. Minimum 44×44px touch target enforced via padding on the button element.\n\n---\n\n### 2.12 `Textarea`\n\n**Role:** Multi-line notes input with live character counting.\n\n**Props:**\n```\nid:               string\nvalue:            string\nplaceholder?:     string\nrows?:            number           // default: 4\nhasError:         bool\nariaDescribedBy?: string\nonChange:         (value: string) => void\nonBlur:           () => void\n```\n\n**No `maxlength` attribute** — the character counter is the feedback mechanism. V-08 error triggers both on blur and in real-time when `value.length > 280`.\n\n---\n\n### 2.13 `CharacterCounter`\n\n**Role:** Live counter display below the Notes textarea.\n\n**Props:**\n```\ncurrent:          number\nmax:              number           // 280\n```\n\n**Renders:** `<span aria-live=\"polite\">{current} / {max}</span>`\n\n**Token binding:** `text-secondary` (`ink-600`) at ≤280; `error` (`red-500`) at >280.\n\n---\n\n### 2.14 `FieldError`\n\n**Role:** Inline error message below an input. Conditionally rendered.\n\n**Props:**\n```\nid:               string            // e.g. \"title-error\"\nmessage:          string | null\n```\n\n**Renders:** `<span id={id} role=\"alert\">{message}</span>` only when `message` is non-null.\n\n---\n\n### 2.15 `OptionalBadge`\n\n**Role:** Small inline pill indicating a field is optional.\n\n**Props:** none (static content \"Optional\")\n\n**Token binding:** `text-secondary` text, `surface-secondary` background, `border-radius: small (8px)`.\n\n---\n\n### 2.16 `FormActions`\n\n**Role:** Layout container for Cancel and Submit buttons. Handles responsive stacking.\n\n**Props:**\n```\nmode:             'add' | 'edit'\nonCancel:         () => void\nonSubmit:         (e: Event) => void\nisSubmitting?:    bool\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2.17 `SubmitButton`\n\n**Role:** Primary form submission CTA.\n\n**Props:**\n```\nmode:             'add' | 'edit'\ndisabled?:        bool\n```\n\n**Label:** `\"Save Bookmark\"` (add) / `\"Update Bookmark\"` (edit)\n\n**Token binding:** `cta-primary` background, `text-on-cta` text. Hover → `cta-hover`.\n\n**Minimum height:** 44px. Full-width on mobile (`< 768px`).\n\n---\n\n### 2.18 `CancelButton`\n\n**Role:** Secondary ghost/text button. Triggers dirty-check before navigation.\n\n**Props:**\n```\nonClick:          () => void\n```\n\n**Minimum height:** 44px. Full-width on mobile (`< 768px`).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Layout Rules\n\n### 3.1 Page-Level Layout\n\n```\n┌────────────────────── viewport ──────────────────────┐\n│                     background-primary                │\n│                                                       │\n│            ┌───────────── 480px max ─────────────┐   │\n│            │  PageHeader                          │   │\n│            │  ─────────────────────────────────  │   │\n│            │  [DirtyFormWarningBar — conditional] │   │\n│            │  ─────────────────────────────────  │   │\n│            │  BookmarkForm                        │   │\n│            │    FieldGroup: Title                 │   │\n│            │    FieldGroup: URL                   │   │\n│            │    FieldGroup: Tags                  │   │\n│            │    FieldGroup: Notes                 │   │\n│            │    FormActions                       │   │\n│            └──────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                                       │\n└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n**Centering mechanism:** `margin: 0 auto` on the form container. `padding: 0 16px` always applied to prevent flush-to-edge rendering. On mobile this padding becomes the effective side margin.\n\n**Vertical rhythm:** `gap: 24px` between FieldGroups within the form. `gap: 32px` between PageHeader and form. `gap: 16px` between PageHeader back link and `<h1>`.\n\n### 3.2 FieldGroup Internal Layout\n\n```\n[Label]                           ← text-primary, label typography\n[Input / TagInputField / Textarea]\n[Helper text OR Error message]    ← 4px gap below input\n[Character counter]               ← bottom-right aligned (Notes only)\n```\n\nVertical stack, no horizontal splitting within a field group.\n\n### 3.3 FormActions Layout\n\n**Desktop (≥ 768px):**\n```\n[ Cancel (ghost, left) ───────────── Submit (primary, right) ]\n```\n`display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;`\n\n**Mobile (< 768px):**\n```\n[ Submit (full-width, primary)  ]\n[ Cancel (full-width, ghost)    ]\n```\n`display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px;`\nSubmit renders first in DOM and visually (top of stack).\n\n### 3.4 TagChip Layout\n\n`display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px;` within `TagChipList`. Each chip: `border-radius: small (8px)`, `padding: 4px 8px`, minimum 44px height touch target on dismiss button.\n\n### 3.5 DirtyFormWarningBar Layout\n\nFull-width relative to the centered form container (480px / full mobile width). Horizontal flex row:\n\n```\n[ ⚠ icon │ message text (flex-grow) │ [Discard] │ [Keep editing] ]\n```\n\n`padding: 12px 16px`, `gap: 12px` between children. Sits between `PageHeader` and `BookmarkForm` in document flow.\n\n### 3.6 CharacterCounter Alignment\n\n`display: flex; justify-content: flex-end;` below the `Textarea`. Not part of the `FieldError` slot — exists as a sibling. When V-08 error is active, both the counter (in error colour) and the `FieldError` message are visible simultaneously.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Token Bindings\n\n### 4.1 Colour Tokens\n\n| Component / Element | Token | Resolved Value |\n|---|---|---|\n| Page background | `background-primary` | `#F8F9FB` (ink-0) |\n| Form surface | `surface-primary` | `#FFFFFF` |\n| Input background | `surface-input` | `#FFFFFF` |\n| Optional badge background | `surface-secondary` | `#EEF1F5` (ink-50) |\n| Input border (default) | `border-default` | `#D6DBE3` (ink-100) |\n| Input border (focus) | `border-focus` | `#4F6AFF` (indigo-500) |\n| Input border (error) | `border-error` | `#E53E3E` (red-500) |\n| Label text | `text-primary` | `#0D0F12` (ink-950) |\n| Helper text | `text-secondary` | `#3A414D` (ink-600) |\n| Placeholder text | `text-disabled` | `#8C95A3` (ink-300) |\n| Error message text | `error` | `#E53E3E` (red-500) |\n| Counter text (≤280) | `text-secondary` | `#3A414D` (ink-600) |\n| Counter text (>280) | `error` | `#E53E3E` (red-500) |\n| Primary button bg | `cta-primary` | `#4F6AFF` (indigo-500) |\n| Primary button bg (hover) | `cta-hover` | `#3A54E8` (indigo-600) |\n| Primary button text | `text-on-cta` | `#FFFFFF` |\n| Cancel button text | `cta-primary` | `#4F6AFF` (indigo-500) |\n| Warning bar background | `warning` | `#F5A623` (amber-400) |\n| Warning bar text | `text-primary` | `#0D0F12` (ink-950) |\n| Tag chip background | `surface-secondary` | `#EEF1F5` (ink-50) |\n| Tag chip text | `text-primary` | `#0D0F12` (ink-950) |\n| Back link text | `cta-primary` | `#4F6AFF` (indigo-500) |\n| Page `<h1>` text | `text-primary` | `#0D0F12` (ink-950) |\n\n> ⚠ **Contrast flags (carry forward from research brief):**\n> - `error` (`#E53E3E`) on white: validate against WCAG AA 4.5:1. Use `red-600` if failing.\n> - `warning` (`#F5A623`) background with `text-primary` (`#0D0F12`): validate. Supplement with `⚠` icon (non-colour indicator).\n\n### 4.2 Typography Tokens\n\n| Element | Scale Role | Size | Weight |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `<h1>` (page title) | `heading-2` | 24px | 700 |\n| `<h1>` (not-found state) | `heading-2` | 24px | 700 |\n| Field labels | `label` | 12px | 500 |\n| Input text | `body` | 14px | 400 |\n| Placeholder text | `body` | 14px | 400 |\n| Helper text | `small` | 11px | 400 |\n| Error messages | `small` | 11px | 400 |\n| Character counter | `small` | 11px | 400 |\n| Tag chip labels | `label` | 12px | 500 |\n| Optional badge text | `label` | 12px | 500 |\n| Primary button | `label` | 12px | 500 |\n| Cancel button | `label` | 12px | 500 |\n| Back link | `body` | 14px | 400 |\n| Warning bar message | `body` | 14px | 400 |\n\n### 4.3 Spacing Tokens\n\n| Context | Token Value | Applied Spacing |\n|---|---|---|\n| Side padding (form container) | 16px | Always applied |\n| Vertical gap between FieldGroups | 24px | `gap: 24px` on form column |\n| Label → input gap | 4px | Within `FieldGroup` |\n| Input → error/helper gap | 4px | Within `FieldGroup` |\n| PageHeader → form gap | 32px | Between header block and form |\n| Back link → `<h1>` gap | 8px | Within `PageHeader` |\n| FormActions top margin | 32px | Above action row |\n| Tag chip internal padding | `4px 8px` | Chip pill |\n| Tag chip row gap | 8px | `gap: 8px` in chip list |\n| Warning bar padding | `12px 16px` | Bar root element |\n| Warning bar child gap | 12px | Between icon / text / buttons |\n| FormActions button gap (mobile stack) | 12px | `gap: 12px` |\n\n### 4.4 Border Radius Tokens\n\n| Element | Token | Value |\n|---|---|---|\n| Text inputs, URL input, Textarea | `medium` | 12px |\n| Tag chips | `small` | 8px |\n| Optional badge | `small` | 8px |\n| Submit button | `medium` | 12px |\n| Cancel button | `medium` | 12px |\n| Warning bar | `small` | 8px |\n\n### 4.5 Elevation Tokens\n\n| Element | Level | Shadow |\n|---|---|---|\n| Text inputs (default) | `0` | none |\n| Form container | `0` | none |\n| Warning bar | `1` | `0 1px 3px rgba(13,15,18,0.08)` |\n\n### 4.6 Focus Ring Token\n\nAll interactive elements:\n```\noutline: 2px solid cta-primary (#4F6AFF)\noutline-offset: 2px\n```\nApplied on `:focus-visible` only (not `:focus`) to prevent mouse-click outline noise.\n\n### 4.7 Motion Tokens\n\n| Animation | Duration | Easing | Applied To |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Warning bar enter | `normal` (200ms) | `ease-out` | Fade + slide-down |\n| Warning bar exit | `normal` (200ms) | `ease-out` | Fade + slide-up |\n| Input border colour transition | `fast` (100ms) | `ease-out` | `border-color` on state change |\n| Error message appear | `fast` (100ms) | `ease-out` | Opacity 0→1 |\n| Button hover | `fast` (100ms) | `ease-out` | `background-color` |\n\n### 4.8 Touch Target Token\n\nAll interactive elements:\n```\nmin-height: 44px    (touch_targets.minimum_height)\nmin-width:  44px    (touch_targets.minimum_width)\n```\nApplied via padding expansion on visually smaller elements (tag chip dismiss button, cancel text button).\n\n### 4.9 Z-Index Tokens\n\n| Element | Token | Value |\n|---|---|---|\n| Toast (success, page-level) | `toast` | 1300 |\n| Warning bar | inline flow | no z-index (in-document, not overlay) |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Responsive Breakpoints\n\n**Breakpoint definitions (from design tokens):**\n\n| Name | Value | Condition |\n|---|---|---|\n| `mobile` | 640px | `max-width: 639px` |\n| `tablet` | 768px | `min-width: 768px` |\n| `desktop` | 1024px | `min-width: 1024px` |\n\n### 5.1 Layout Breakpoint Behaviour\n\n| Property | `< 768px` (mobile) | `≥ 768px` (tablet+) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Form container width | `100%` | `480px` |\n| Form container margin | `0` | `0 auto` |\n| Side padding | `16px` | `16px` (inside 480px container) |\n| FormActions direction | `flex-column` | `flex-row` |\n| FormActions button width | `100%` (each) | `auto` |\n| Submit button position (stack) | Top (first in visual order) | Right |\n| Cancel button position | Below Submit | Left |\n| Tag chips | `flex-wrap: wrap` (unchanged) | `flex-wrap: wrap` |\n| PageHeader layout | Stacked (back link above `<h1>`) | Stacked (back link above `<h1>`) |\n| Warning bar | Full-width, message may wrap | Full-width, message on one line |\n\n### 5.2 Form Container Centering CSS Logic\n\n```css\n/* Form centering container */\n.form-centering-wrapper {\n  width: 100%;\n  max-width: 480px;\n  margin: 0 auto;\n  padding: 0 16px;\n  box-sizing: border-box;\n}\n```\n\nOn `< 768px`: `max-width` has no effect — container is already `100% - 32px`. On `≥ 768px`: container locks to 480px and centers.\n\n### 5.3 Component-Level Responsive Overrides\n\n#### `FormActions`\n\n```\n// Mobile (< 768px)\ndisplay: flex;\nflex-direction: column;\ngap: 12px;\n\n  .submit-button { order: 1; width: 100%; }\n  .cancel-button { order: 2; width: 100%; }\n\n// Tablet+ (≥ 768px)\ndisplay: flex;\nflex-direction: row;\njustify-content: space-between;\nalign-items: center;\n\n  .cancel-button { /* left, auto width */ }\n  .submit-button { /* right, auto width */ }\n```\n\n#### `DirtyFormWarningBar`\n\n```\n// Mobile (< 768px)\nflex-wrap: wrap;\n.warning-actions { width: 100%; justify-content: flex-end; }\n\n// Tablet+ (≥ 768px)\nflex-wrap: nowrap;\nsingle-row layout\n```\n\n#### `Textarea`\n\n```\n// Mobile (< 768px)\nrows: 4 (unchanged)\nresize: vertical (allow user resize)\n\n// Tablet+ (≥ 768px)\nrows: 4 (unchanged)\nresize: vertical\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Validation State Machine (Implementation Reference)\n\n### 6.1 Per-Field States\n\n| State | Error Visible | Border | Triggered By |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `PRISTINE` | No | `border-default` | Initial render |\n| `TOUCHED_VALID` | No | `border-default` | Blur, value passes validation |\n| `TOUCHED_INVALID` | Yes | `border-error` | Blur, value fails validation |\n| `SUBMIT_FORCED_VALID` | No | `border-default` | Submit with valid value |\n| `SUBMIT_FORCED_INVALID` | Yes | `border-error` | Submit with invalid value (was PRISTINE) |\n\n### 6.2 Validation Rules Summary\n\n| Field | Rule ID | Condition | Error Message |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Title | V-01/V-02 | Length < 2 or > 120 (after trim) | \"Title must be 2–120 characters.\" |\n| URL | V-03 | Empty | \"URL is required.\" |\n| URL | V-04 | Fails `^https?://` regex | \"Enter a valid URL starting with http:// or https://.\" |\n| Tags | V-07 | Count > 5 | \"Maximum 5 tags allowed.\" |\n| Tags | V-06 | Any tag length > 20 | \"Each tag must be 20 characters or less.\" |\n| Tags | V-05 | Any tag fails `^[a-z0-9-]+$` | \"Tags can only contain letters, numbers, and hyphens.\" |\n| Notes | V-08 | Length > 280 | \"Notes must be 280 characters or less.\" |\n\n**Tag validation priority:** V-07 → V-06 → V-05. Only highest-priority error shown at a time.\n\n**Notes real-time rule:** V-08 triggers on `oninput` when `value.length > 280` (does not wait for blur). Reverts to no-error in real-time when length drops ≤ 280.\n\n### 6.3 Submit Sequence (Pseudocode)\n\n```\nfunction handleSubmit(e):\n  e.preventDefault()\n  \n  mark all fields as TOUCHED\n  run validation on all fields\n  \n  if any field is INVALID:\n    scroll to first invalid field element\n    set programmatic focus on first invalid input\n    return  // stop\n  \n  if mode === 'add':\n    BookmarkStore.create(formValues)\n  else:\n    BookmarkStore.update(bookmarkId, formValues)\n  \n  navigate('/')\n  injectToast(mode === 'add' ? 'Bookmark saved' : 'Bookmark updated')\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Accessibility Bindings Summary\n\n| Component | ARIA / Semantic Requirement |\n|---|---|\n| `<form>` | `novalidate` attribute |\n| `TextInput` (required) | `required`, `aria-required=\"true\"`, `aria-describedby=\"{field}-error\"`, `aria-invalid=\"true\"` when error |\n| `TextInput` (optional) | `aria-describedby=\"{field}-error\"`, `aria-invalid=\"true\"` when error |\n| `FieldError` | `role=\"alert\"`, unique `id=\"{field}-error\"` |\n| `FieldLabel` required indicator | `<span aria-hidden=\"true\">*</span>` + visually-hidden `\" (required)\"` |\n| `CharacterCounter` | `aria-live=\"polite\"` |\n| `DirtyFormWarningBar` | `role=\"alert\"` on root element |\n| `TagChip` dismiss button | `aria-label=\"Remove tag: {tagname}\"` |\n| Toast (page-level) | `role=\"status\"`, `aria-live=\"polite\"` |\n| Back link | Standard `<a>` with descriptive text |\n| `PageTitle` | `<h1>`, single per page |\n\n**Tab order (explicit):**\n1. Back link\n2. Warning bar \"Discard\" button (if bar visible)\n3. Warning bar \"Keep editing\" button (if bar visible)\n4. Title input\n5. URL input\n6. Tags text input\n7. Tag chip dismiss buttons (in chip render order)\n8. Notes textarea\n9. Cancel button\n10. Submit button\n\n---\n\n## 8. Component Communication Map\n\n```\nAddEditBookmarkPage\n│\n├── owns: formValues, fieldMeta, isDirty, showWarningBar, mode\n│\n├──► PageHeader (props: mode)\n├──► DirtyFormWarningBar (props: visible, onDiscard, onKeepEditing)\n├──► NotFoundState (rendered if mode === 'not-found')\n└──► BookmarkForm\n     │   (props: values, fieldMeta, mode, handlers)\n     │\n     ├──► FieldGroup[Title] → TextInput\n     │     └── onChange / onBlur → bubbles to AddEditBookmarkPage\n     │\n     ├──► FieldGroup[URL] → TextInput + HttpAdvisory\n     │     └── onChange / onBlur → bubbles to AddEditBookmarkPage\n     │\n     ├──► FieldGroup[Tags] → TagInputField\n     │     ├── TagChipList → TagChip[] → DismissButton\n     │     └── TagTextInput → onChange / onBlur / onKeyDown → bubbles\n     │\n     ├──► FieldGroup[Notes] → Textarea + CharacterCounter\n     │     └── onChange / onBlur → bubbles to AddEditBookmarkPage\n     │\n     └──► FormActions\n          ├── CancelButton → onCancel → AddEditBookmarkPage dirty check\n          └── SubmitButton → onSubmit → AddEditBookmark"
}